We run Gratipay via [queue management](http://www.amazon.com/-/dp/1935401009),
and we also practice chat-ops. We use a short-hand in [IRC](/appendices/chat)
inspired by [Inbox Zero](http://www.43folders.com/2006/03/13/inbox-zero) to
signal what queue we're each paying to and what its status is. It's simple!
Just say: `Queue 0`. That tells the rest of us what queue you're paying
attention to and how full it is. Some common queues are
[Support](https://gratipay.freshdesk.com/helpdesk/tickets),
[Twitter](https://gratipay.freshdesk.com/social/streams),
[WIP](https://github.com/gratipay/gratipay.com/pulls?q=is%3Aopen+is%3Apr+label%3A%223+-+Work+in+Progress%22),
[Review](https://github.com/gratipay/gratipay.com/pulls?q=is%3Aopen+is%3Apr+label%3A%224+-+Review%22),
Inbox (for our personal email inbox), GitHub (for our personal GitHub
notifications queue), and ... Lunch! `Lunch 1` means I'm going to lunch and
`Lunch 0` means I'm back. :D
